'ad-table-lite'
'table-name'
'Name of the table. Name has to be so that it'
' can be a valid javascript variable name. Make sure that your scope does not have'
'a property with the same name as the tree-name'
'column-definition'
'Path to the object (array) that has all the column definitions. '
'Look at more info for details on how to build columnDefinition object'
'local-data-source'
'Array of items to be rendered in table'
'page-sizes'
'[10, 25, 50]'
'Available page sizes'
'page-size'
'10'
'Number'
'Starting page size, defaults to first in page-sizes'
'disable-paging'
'false'
'Boolean'
'shows all the items in local-data-source'
'enable-column-search'
'shows column search inputs. Works in combination with '
'<code>columnSearchProperty</code> on columnDefinition'
'table-classes'
'"table"'
'these classes will be applied to the table tag. '
'Ex (<code>table-classes: "table table-bordered"</code>)'
'pagination-btn-group-classes'
'"pagination pagination-sm"'
'these classes will be applied to the pagination pagination ul tag. '
'Ex (<code>pagination-btn-group-classes="pagination pagination-xs"</code>)'
'draggable'
'NA'
'enables drag & drop on the table rows within and across pages'
'on-drag-change'
'Function'
'callback function which fires when a change occurs due to a '
'drag and drop, the parameters for the callback are position before drag,'
'position after drag & the data being moved'
'selected-items'
'Path to the array that will hold selected items. '
'<code>ex: selected-items="models.selectedCars"</code>. If speecified, the rows will be'
' selectable by checkbox. selected rows will have <code>ad-selected</code> class on it. '
'You can target this class in your css to apply custom styling to the selected rows.'
'row-class-provider'
'Path to the function that returns row class'
'<code>row-class-provider="checkRowSelected"</code>. The function '
'will get called with row item and the index. You can do any logic on row'
'and return a class string. That class will be applied to the row. Good usecase'
'is if you want to apply primary class to the selected rows. We recommend you return'
'Default bootstrap classes (<code>"active", "success", "warning", "danger", "info"</code>)'
'search-text'
'The text to search by'
'<code>ex: search-text="models.searchText"</code>. If speecified, the rows'
' will be searched and filtered by the content and the search enabled columns '
'btn-classes'
'btn btn-default'
'classes to be applied to dropdown button. '
'<code>Ex: btn-classes="btn btn-primary btn-sm"</code>'
'table-max-height'
'auto'
'This property makes the table scrollable. The header becomes fixed at top. '
'Pass in any css max-height property. EX: <code>table-max-height="157px"</code>'
'table-fixed-height'
'This property makes the table fixed height. The header becomes fixed at top. '
'Pass in any css max-height property. EX: <code>table-fixed-height="157px"</code>'
'items-not-found-message'
'Message that will be shown in case of empty table'
'on-click-sort-direction'
'ASC'
'Which direction to sort first when column is clicked. '
'EX: <code>on-click-sort-direction="DEC"</code>'
'initial-sort-key'
'DEC'
'Sort key to use on initialization. '
'EX: <code>initial-sort-key="name"</code>'
'initial-sort-direction'
'Which direction to sort the initial-sort-key. '
'EX: <code>initial-sort-direction="DEC"</code>'
'snug-sort-icons'
'false'
'Boolean'
'If true, the sort icons will be right next to header text. '
'Good for limited real estate scenarios.'
'row-expand-template'
'Template for row expand. Generally used for more info or in-place edit.'
'row-expand-callback'
'Function'
'callback for row expand. Useful for lazy loading extra information on expand.'
'on-row-click'
'This function gets called with item and event properties when row is clicked.'
'ex: <code>on-row-click="rowClicked"</code>'

'Function'
'Callback for drag begin event. It fires when a drag starts. it should take 3 '
'parameters <code>$data, $dragElement, $event</code>. <strong>Note:</strong> Use <code>'
'$dragElement.el</code>to get the element.'

'Callback for drag end event. It fires when a drag has ended, always after the'

'<strong>Note:</strong> Use <code>$dragElement.el</code> to get the actual element.'

'<strong>Note:</strong> Use <code>$dragElement/$dropElement.el</code> to get the element.'

'ad-drop-leave'
'Callback for the drop leave event. It fires drag element leaves drop element. '

'simply target <code>ad-drop-over</code> class.'
